# Table Seating Planner

## Summary
TableSeatingPlanner is the main card of the package: a drag-and-drop seating chart for a wedding or event. It carries the event identity (`eventTitle`, `eventDate`, `venue`, `eventLogo`, plus `hosts = linksToMany(Host)` with a computed `hostNames` header string), the guest list (`guests = linksToMany(Guest)`), and the room itself (`tables = containsMany(Table)` and `fixtures = containsMany(Fixture)`), with each Table tracking its own seated guests. Supporting fields handle a floor-plan underlay image (`floorPlanURL` with position, size, opacity, and lock fields), invitation and seating messages, and a generated event poster (`poster`, `posterPrompt`, `posterAspect`).

## Import
```js
import { TableSeatingPlanner } from '../table-seating-planner';
```

## Usage
TableSeatingPlanner is a card, so consuming cards link to it rather than containing it:

```js
import { CardDef, field, linksTo } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { TableSeatingPlanner } from '../table-seating-planner';

export class WeddingBinder extends CardDef {
  @field seatingPlan = linksTo(TableSeatingPlanner);
}
```

## Template Usage
```handlebars
<@fields.seatingPlan />
```
Renders the linked plan; open it isolated to work on the full seating canvas.
